it live because you see them sometimes debug live or change things on the fly.

00:10:50.000 --> 00:10:57.280
It also helped a lot with, I think, my own imposter syndrome. Just seeing that

00:10:57.919 --> 00:11:02.239
they also get tripped up and they also use the pipe instead of plus whenever they're

00:11:02.239 --> 00:11:08.320
using ggplot2, that kind of thing. So yeah, definitely have noticed a bigger

00:11:08.320 --> 00:11:13.119
shift into video and it's very much a welcome one, at least for me.

00:11:16.239 --> 00:11:20.880
Definitely, I see a few people commenting about that in the chat too. I know Julia

00:11:20.880 --> 00:11:26.640
Silgi from our studio does that quite a bit. I see there's an anonymous question that came

00:11:26.640 --> 00:11:33.840
through. A great question that's, what are some pitfalls that you would give advice on to avoid

00:11:33.840 --> 00:11:40.880
for the first data analyst in a company with no data pipeline that wants to make data-driven decisions?

00:11:41.760 --> 00:11:55.119
Yeah, I think trying to do too much is a bad play. I think also making sure that you have a lot of

00:11:55.119 --> 00:12:04.960
face time with the stakeholders is important. I think, you know, I had sort of many ideas of what

00:12:05.840 --> 00:12:12.239
I wanted to do with this data, but when you actually sit down with the people that will

00:12:12.239 --> 00:12:20.080
be using this data, it looks differently. So I think just making sure you have that

00:12:20.080 --> 00:12:26.400
face time, that you do your due diligence in terms of, you know, what your tech stack is

00:12:26.400 --> 00:12:35.440
going to look like, make sure you right from the get-go have reproducibility and code quality

00:12:36.239 --> 00:12:43.359
in mind as you're building out those pipelines are all important considerations, I think.

00:12:46.400 --> 00:12:52.400
Definitely, thank you. Jeffrey, I see you had a question that I'd love to pass over to you to

00:12:52.400 --> 00:12:56.799
ask live, and I figured I'd say this too. If people want to introduce yourselves, I know it's

