data scientists involves just a little bit more, you know, engineering work, ML ops, DevOps sort of

00:21:23.760 --> 00:21:35.680
work. But honestly, I use them interchangeably, but others might have differing thoughts on that.

00:21:41.439 --> 00:21:48.000
Yeah, I feel like a lot of us do use them interchangeably. I know in past conversations,

00:21:48.239 --> 00:21:55.520
we've talked a bit about data analysts more so reporting the data.

00:21:57.280 --> 00:22:00.560
I don't know if anyone has other thoughts you want to add there.

00:22:06.719 --> 00:22:10.719
Feel free to raise your hands, too, if you want to, like, I know it's hard with 100 people to

00:22:10.719 --> 00:22:20.400
just jump in. So, Balak, did you want to add anything? Yes, I recently attended some lectures

00:22:20.400 --> 00:22:29.199
about AI ML. And in those lectures, it was explained in a very good way, the difference

00:22:29.199 --> 00:22:36.319
between data scientists and data engineers. Basically, data scientists are those people

00:22:36.319 --> 00:22:45.920
who understand the distribution about the data, and they figure out based on the distribution,

00:22:45.920 --> 00:22:57.520
what class of AI ML algorithms would be suitable to handle that particular problem. So, this is

00:22:57.520 --> 00:23:04.319
mostly done by data scientists, because there are multiple classes of AI ML algorithms that you can

00:23:04.319 --> 00:23:12.479
use to solve your problem. And that thing and that work is done by data scientists to help you

00:23:13.199 --> 00:23:17.920
by understanding your data, by looking into the data, about the distribution of the data,

00:23:17.920 --> 00:23:24.959
you can figure out what class of algorithm is best suited to solve your specific problem.

00:23:25.599 --> 00:23:34.000
And once that is decided, then the data engineers or ML engineers, they then solve

00:23:34.000 --> 00:23:39.920
the optimization problem. So, within that specific class of algorithms, they figure out which

00:23:41.680 --> 00:23:48.319
specific algorithm with specific configurations, this algorithm,

00:23:48.319 --> 00:23:52.400
which algorithm is going to perform the best for that specific set of data.

